Cut bread into 2 inch squares and place into well-greased 9 x 13 inch casserole dish. Add broccoli, ham and cheese (cut into bite-size pieces). In a separate bowl, add milk to eggs and beat well. Add salt, pepper and mustard. Pour egg mixture over bread mixture in casserole. Refrigerate overnight. Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour in 350 degree F oven.